1
00:00:10,700 --> 00:00:12,867
<i>You're getting back to normal,
Emma.</i>

2
00:00:13,000 --> 00:00:14,200
<i> You're all better.</i>

3
00:00:14,333 --> 00:00:17,167
<i>I wouldn't have healed without
your support.</i>

4
00:00:17,300 --> 00:00:18,333
<i> Thank you, Logan.</i>

5
00:00:18,467 --> 00:00:20,200
<i> Thank you so much.</i>

6
00:00:20,333 --> 00:00:21,667
<i> Can I see them?</i>

7
00:00:21,800 --> 00:00:22,867
<i>I don't think this is
the right time.</i>

8
00:00:23,000 --> 00:00:24,667
<i> Surprise!</i>

9
00:00:24,800 --> 00:00:26,700
<i>Will you take this journey
with me?</i>

10
00:00:26,833 --> 00:00:29,267
<i> Will you marry me, Dan?</i>

11
00:00:29,400 --> 00:00:30,000
<i> Yes, Jade.</i>

12
00:00:30,133 --> 00:00:31,267
<i> I will marry you.</i>

13
00:00:31,400 --> 00:00:32,233
<i> Mom?</i>

14
00:00:32,367 --> 00:00:33,300
<i> Mom?</i>

15
00:00:33,433 --> 00:00:34,933
<i> I think I saw Mom.</i>

16
00:00:35,100 --> 00:00:36,600
<i> Maybe I just saw it wrong.</i>

17
00:00:36,733 --> 00:00:38,567
<i>I hope she never shows up to me.</i>

18
00:00:38,700 --> 00:00:40,467
<i>My family was taken away
from me.</i>

19
00:00:40,600 --> 00:00:41,867
<i> I couldn't do anything.</i>

20
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:43,300
<i> You can do something.</i>

21
00:00:43,433 --> 00:00:44,467
<i> We can do something.</i>

22
00:00:44,600 --> 00:00:46,700
<i> I want you both to be happy.</i>

23
00:00:46,833 --> 00:00:48,233
<i> Yes, I was surprised.</i>

24
00:00:48,367 --> 00:00:51,533
<i>But that doesn't mean
I'll back out.</i>

25
00:00:51,667 --> 00:00:53,300
<i> How dare you!</i>

26
00:01:33,000 --> 00:01:33,833
Mom?

27
00:01:37,767 --> 00:01:39,200
You shameless pigs.

28
00:01:41,100 --> 00:01:46,033
I wouldn't know what happened if
Kutsy and Wiro didn't tell me.

29
00:01:47,533 --> 00:01:49,067
I don't understand, Jade.

30
00:01:49,200 --> 00:01:52,200
You told me everything
is fine here.

31
00:01:52,333 --> 00:01:55,100
It turns out that something bad
is already happening to Emma.

32
00:01:55,233 --> 00:01:58,133
You're betraying
your own sister!

33
00:01:58,267 --> 00:02:02,167
Mom, Wiro told us you're
hypertensive.

34
00:02:02,300 --> 00:02:04,267
We didn't tell you
what was happening

35
00:02:04,400 --> 00:02:06,633
because we didn't want you
to get harmed.

36
00:02:06,767 --> 00:02:09,867
Jade didn't do anything wrong,
Mom.

37
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:14,300
She doesn't want anything
but for Emma to get better.

38
00:02:14,467 --> 00:02:17,333
But it was Emma who went away.

39
00:02:17,467 --> 00:02:19,267
I know I did wrong.

40
00:02:19,400 --> 00:02:21,400
So, please forgive me, Mom.

41
00:02:21,533 --> 00:02:24,767
But I was upset.

42
00:02:24,900 --> 00:02:27,533
Emma left us without a word,
Mom!

43
00:02:27,667 --> 00:02:31,033
She left you without a word?
Are you sure she left?

44
00:02:31,167 --> 00:02:32,900
Emma isn't that type of person!

45
00:02:33,033 --> 00:02:34,933
She will never do that.

46
00:02:35,067 --> 00:02:37,900
She won't leave you,
especially Mookie.

47
00:02:38,033 --> 00:02:40,000
Did you look for her?

48
00:02:40,133 --> 00:02:41,533
- I tried.
- Shut up!

49
00:02:41,667 --> 00:02:45,300
I'm not done yet!
I'm not talking to you!

50
00:02:45,433 --> 00:02:47,933
Okay, let's say she left.

51
00:02:48,100 --> 00:02:49,467
Is that a valid reason?

52
00:02:49,600 --> 00:02:52,167
Is that a reason
to cheat on her?

53
00:02:52,300 --> 00:02:55,000
To replace her with her own
sister?

54
00:02:55,133 --> 00:02:59,367
What if something bad
is happening to Emma?

55
00:02:59,500 --> 00:03:04,400
Jade has been taking care
of Mookie tirelessly, Mom.

56
00:03:04,533 --> 00:03:07,000
She has become Mookie's mother.

57
00:03:07,133 --> 00:03:10,867
So you can't blame me if I fell
with Jade.

58
00:03:12,200 --> 00:03:13,933
Darn you!

59
00:03:14,067 --> 00:03:15,967
Traitor!

60
00:03:16,100 --> 00:03:21,133
Emma has never given up on you.

61
00:03:21,300 --> 00:03:24,233
I told her many times

62
00:03:24,367 --> 00:03:27,600
that she didn't deserve someone
like you.

63
00:03:27,733 --> 00:03:30,133
But Emma fought for you.

64
00:03:30,267 --> 00:03:33,400
Yet you gave up on her just like
that.

65
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:39,267
You're such a weak man.

66
00:03:39,400 --> 00:03:41,800
You're a useless husband!

67
00:03:43,267 --> 00:03:44,533
Mom.

68
00:03:44,667 --> 00:03:45,700
You, too.

69
00:03:45,833 --> 00:03:46,500
Jade.

70
00:03:47,600 --> 00:03:52,800
I regret taking your side back
then.

71
00:03:52,933 --> 00:03:56,633
I took your side over Emma's.

72
00:03:56,800 --> 00:03:59,233
Poor Emma.

73
00:03:59,367 --> 00:04:02,833
Maybe her mind could no longer
take everything

74
00:04:02,967 --> 00:04:05,300
she went through.

75
00:04:05,433 --> 00:04:08,300
And this is what you do to her?

76
00:04:09,733 --> 00:04:11,267
You cheated on her!

77
00:04:13,033 --> 00:04:15,333
If she cheated on you,

78
00:04:15,467 --> 00:04:18,700
she can also do that to me
despite being her sister.

79
00:04:21,167 --> 00:04:27,400
I'm sure Jade did that to you
because she knows you're weak.

80
00:04:27,567 --> 00:04:29,967
She can scare you.

81
00:04:30,100 --> 00:04:31,867
She can make you fold.

82
00:04:33,567 --> 00:04:35,433
She's worse than Olive.

83
00:04:35,567 --> 00:04:37,433
She didn't only take Mookie.

84
00:04:37,567 --> 00:04:38,667
Danilo, too.

85
00:04:40,800 --> 00:04:45,700
If you think about it, Jade is
not only the one to blame.

86
00:04:47,667 --> 00:04:51,733
Your husband wouldn't get stolen
if he didn't want to.

87
00:04:53,067 --> 00:04:54,167
He gave in!

88
00:04:55,900 --> 00:05:00,333
Remember, your husband cheated
on you.

89
00:05:00,500 --> 00:05:03,133
The nerve of you.

90
00:05:05,100 --> 00:05:07,167
Pigs.

91
00:05:07,300 --> 00:05:09,800
How dare you do that
while I was away.

92
00:05:11,767 --> 00:05:15,167
And I couldn't do anything.

93
00:05:15,300 --> 00:05:17,200
I couldn't do anything
for my daughter.

94
00:05:17,333 --> 00:05:19,667
I wasn't by Emma's side
to help her.

95
00:05:19,800 --> 00:05:21,433
And this is what you did to her.

96
00:05:21,567 --> 00:05:23,000
Animals.

97
00:05:23,133 --> 00:05:26,933
The nerve of both of you.

98
00:05:27,067 --> 00:05:28,833
Pigs.

99
00:05:28,967 --> 00:05:30,233
Why did you do that?

100
00:05:30,367 --> 00:05:32,633
Why did you do this to my child?

101
00:05:36,533 --> 00:05:38,067
Forgive me.

102
00:05:42,233 --> 00:05:44,467
Forgive me, Emma.

103
00:06:15,633 --> 00:06:18,200
Men like him are not worth
returning to.

104
00:06:21,000 --> 00:06:24,833
He threw away our relationship
just like that.

105
00:06:24,967 --> 00:06:27,267
I stood up for him to Mom.

106
00:06:27,400 --> 00:06:30,567
And he cheated on me in return.
He betrayed me.

107
00:06:30,700 --> 00:06:32,967
But this isn't over yet.

108
00:06:33,100 --> 00:06:36,833
I will show Jade that she fought
the wrong person.

109
00:06:36,967 --> 00:06:39,967
I can't confront her yet.

110
00:06:40,100 --> 00:06:43,633
But I'll do everything
to change my life.

111
00:06:45,733 --> 00:06:47,300
I will fight, Logan.

112
00:06:50,133 --> 00:06:53,100
I will prepare for our face-off.

113
00:06:54,333 --> 00:06:58,167
And I will make them feel
the pain I have right now.

114
00:07:03,000 --> 00:07:04,200
So then...

115
00:07:07,967 --> 00:07:09,600
let's toast to that.

116
00:07:12,567 --> 00:07:14,167
To a new Emma.

117
00:07:34,833 --> 00:07:36,133
Mom, wait.

118
00:07:36,967 --> 00:07:41,000
I will find a new place
first thing in the morning.

119
00:07:41,133 --> 00:07:44,500
I'm moving out of your house.

120
00:07:44,633 --> 00:07:46,700
Mom, don't get mad at me.

121
00:07:48,000 --> 00:07:49,567
I'm your daughter, too.

122
00:07:51,100 --> 00:07:53,167
Just because you're my
daughter doesn't mean

123
00:07:53,433 --> 00:07:56,333
I'll tolerate all your
wrongdoings.

124
00:07:57,233 --> 00:08:01,367
I've done nothing but think
about you and Olive all my life.

125
00:08:01,500 --> 00:08:03,333
And look for you.

126
00:08:03,467 --> 00:08:08,300
Emma was by my side, but you
were the ones I was thinking of.

127
00:08:12,567 --> 00:08:14,300
And now Emma's gone.

128
00:08:15,900 --> 00:08:21,300
I've realized I have so many
shortcomings with her.

129
00:08:23,833 --> 00:08:25,600
I'll look for my daughter.

130
00:08:26,733 --> 00:08:28,867
I'll fix her family.

131
00:08:30,233 --> 00:08:32,067
Wait. What do you mean?

132
00:08:33,233 --> 00:08:36,333
You will return Emma
to Danilo and Mookie?

133
00:08:37,700 --> 00:08:39,500
Why not?

134
00:08:39,633 --> 00:08:41,767
They are family.

135
00:08:41,900 --> 00:08:43,467
Emma's gone!

136
00:08:45,333 --> 00:08:47,900
I'm now Danilo and Mookie's
family!

137
00:08:53,700 --> 00:08:54,833
I'm so sorry, Mom.

138
00:08:56,300 --> 00:08:59,267
I'm sorry.
I didn't mean to do that.

139
00:09:02,833 --> 00:09:05,133
You stole Emma's family.

140
00:09:05,267 --> 00:09:09,433
And now you're raising
your voice on me.

141
00:09:11,400 --> 00:09:12,400
Grandmother!

142
00:09:14,667 --> 00:09:15,867
Mookie, my grandchild.

143
00:09:24,833 --> 00:09:25,933
How are you?

144
00:09:27,300 --> 00:09:33,700
That wouldn't happen if
Mom didn't leave us.

145
00:09:33,867 --> 00:09:34,633
Right?

146
00:09:38,867 --> 00:09:42,533
Until now,

147
00:09:43,800 --> 00:09:46,733
I still can't believe

148
00:09:46,867 --> 00:09:50,433
that Aunt Jade and Dad
are getting married.

149
00:09:52,967 --> 00:09:57,667
But Aunt Jade has been
good to us, Grandmother.

150
00:09:59,067 --> 00:10:01,767
And she's been doing
things...

151
00:10:01,933 --> 00:10:05,200
things that Mom is supposed
to do.

152
00:10:10,267 --> 00:10:12,000
Sometimes I wonder,

153
00:10:13,600 --> 00:10:15,833
are we betraying Mom?

154
00:10:18,767 --> 00:10:22,100
But does Mom think about us now?

155
00:10:23,233 --> 00:10:24,500
And the pain.

156
00:10:26,000 --> 00:10:29,300
And the pain Dad and I have.

157
00:11:04,900 --> 00:11:06,167
You know what...

158
00:11:06,300 --> 00:11:08,033
I was surprised.

159
00:11:08,200 --> 00:11:09,967
She didn't seem to be Jade.

160
00:11:11,400 --> 00:11:13,467
We noticed that, too.

161
00:11:13,600 --> 00:11:17,067
We thought Jade was a good
person.

162
00:11:17,200 --> 00:11:20,433
But she's worse.

163
00:11:20,567 --> 00:11:21,967
Imagine?

164
00:11:22,100 --> 00:11:24,633
She stole Danilo.

165
00:11:26,100 --> 00:11:29,967
I was reminded of Olive
when she yelled at me.

166
00:11:30,100 --> 00:11:32,133
That was how Olive was.

167
00:11:51,933 --> 00:11:54,100
You opened up to me before.

168
00:11:55,800 --> 00:11:57,767
So you should get to know me,
too.

169
00:12:00,067 --> 00:12:01,067
Do you see this?

170
00:12:02,300 --> 00:12:04,733
I got a bit lucky
when I worked in Japan.

171
00:12:06,067 --> 00:12:09,667
I got some savings and put up
some business.

172
00:12:11,200 --> 00:12:12,500
It's impressive.

173
00:12:12,633 --> 00:12:15,867
You were able to do
this with your efforts.

174
00:12:20,833 --> 00:12:26,433
You have no idea how hard it was
for me to get here.

175
00:12:29,167 --> 00:12:36,333
So I'm telling you as early
as now that I'm not perfect.

176
00:12:37,700 --> 00:12:40,633
Not all my businesses are legal.

177
00:12:42,133 --> 00:12:44,067
But that's my source of income.

178
00:12:45,667 --> 00:12:47,567
Did you know what it gave me?

179
00:12:48,800 --> 00:12:50,133
Power.

180
00:12:51,600 --> 00:12:53,733
That's what I want for you.

181
00:12:54,867 --> 00:12:56,333
You'll bounce back.

182
00:12:58,367 --> 00:13:04,400
So I want you to learn
everything about running

183
00:13:04,533 --> 00:13:05,433
all my businesses.

184
00:13:07,933 --> 00:13:12,600
Isn't what you've done
for me more than enough?

185
00:13:14,100 --> 00:13:16,733
I might not be able to return
all your kindness.

186
00:13:21,300 --> 00:13:23,567
Who said you'll pay?

187
00:13:29,667 --> 00:13:32,800
Did you know that helping you
makes me happy?

188
00:13:37,600 --> 00:13:39,800
Emma, I don't want anyone
to do you bad.

189
00:13:41,267 --> 00:13:44,100
That's why I'll help you
get even with Jade.

190
00:13:45,400 --> 00:13:51,567
As you said, you can't do
that without the ability.

191
00:13:53,367 --> 00:13:58,033
I'll help you prepare
for your reunion.

192
00:14:08,833 --> 00:14:09,533
So?

193
00:14:10,567 --> 00:14:12,933
Haven't you found Emma yet?

194
00:14:13,067 --> 00:14:15,100
Can you do it faster?

195
00:14:15,233 --> 00:14:17,267
Because another annoying person
is here.

196
00:14:19,133 --> 00:14:20,567
Her mother.

197
00:14:21,800 --> 00:14:22,833
Make it quick.

198
00:14:57,500 --> 00:14:59,967
This house is so big.

199
00:15:00,100 --> 00:15:01,933
I didn't know there was also
a room here.

200
00:15:05,067 --> 00:15:06,833
What is Jade doing there?

201
00:15:13,267 --> 00:15:16,467
Ligaya is so annoying.

202
00:15:16,600 --> 00:15:19,367
I wish she never came back.

203
00:15:19,500 --> 00:15:26,267
Because I'm sure she'll ruin
my plans.

204
00:15:26,400 --> 00:15:33,900
She must not know that
Jade died, and I...

205
00:15:36,000 --> 00:15:41,400
Olive Caparas is still
so much alive.

206
00:15:49,633 --> 00:15:51,267
You're Olive?

207
00:15:58,400 --> 00:15:59,633
I was right.

208
00:16:01,133 --> 00:16:02,933
That explains why something
feels strange about you.

209
00:16:03,067 --> 00:16:04,967
You're not Jade.

210
00:16:05,100 --> 00:16:06,900
You're Olive!

211
00:16:08,100 --> 00:16:09,100
Ligaya...

212
00:16:09,233 --> 00:16:10,300
Mom.

213
00:16:10,433 --> 00:16:11,500
Mom.

214
00:16:12,700 --> 00:16:14,433
Mom, wait.

215
00:16:14,567 --> 00:16:16,300
Let me explain.

216
00:16:16,433 --> 00:16:19,400
- Hear me out.
- What does this mean?

217
00:16:20,900 --> 00:16:22,800
Did you kill Jade?

218
00:16:22,933 --> 00:16:24,700
Did you kill your own sister?

219
00:16:24,833 --> 00:16:26,400
- No! No!
- Did you?

220
00:16:26,533 --> 00:16:28,700
No, I can never do that to Jade.

221
00:16:29,967 --> 00:16:32,967
We both fell,
but her fall was worse.

222
00:16:35,400 --> 00:16:38,600
I only pretended because...

223
00:16:38,733 --> 00:16:40,767
I was scared I'd go
to jail again.

224
00:16:42,933 --> 00:16:46,067
Didn't you say you wanted
to make it up to me?

225
00:16:46,200 --> 00:16:47,767
This is the time.

226
00:16:47,900 --> 00:16:50,467
This is your chance
to make it up to me.

227
00:16:50,600 --> 00:16:51,433
Please.

228
00:16:51,567 --> 00:16:54,067
Please, please.
I'm begging you, Mom.

229
00:16:54,200 --> 00:16:57,000
I'm begging you.
Don't tell them about this.

230
00:16:57,133 --> 00:16:59,433
Don't tell them the truth.

231
00:16:59,567 --> 00:17:00,467
Please.

232
00:17:00,600 --> 00:17:05,133
I regret giving you and Jade up
for adoption.

233
00:17:05,267 --> 00:17:08,967
I never expected that you'd be
this evil.

234
00:17:10,000 --> 00:17:12,000
Yes, I love you.

235
00:17:12,133 --> 00:17:13,067
You're my child.

236
00:17:13,200 --> 00:17:14,800
But I love Emma, too.

237
00:17:14,967 --> 00:17:16,533
What you're doing...

238
00:17:19,000 --> 00:17:20,267
is wrong.

239
00:17:20,400 --> 00:17:22,933
You're taking Emma's family
away.

240
00:17:23,067 --> 00:17:25,167
And you're pretending
to be Jade.

241
00:17:25,300 --> 00:17:26,833
You're pretending.

242
00:17:26,967 --> 00:17:29,533
You're so evil!

243
00:17:37,900 --> 00:17:39,100
So, what will you do?

244
00:17:42,067 --> 00:17:43,500
Are you going to expose me?

245
00:17:43,633 --> 00:17:45,900
Are you going to tell them
the truth?

246
00:17:46,033 --> 00:17:50,133
You ruined my life
when you gave me away!

247
00:17:50,300 --> 00:17:54,500
I was never happy
with my adoptive parents!

248
00:17:54,633 --> 00:17:58,167
This is the first time
I've felt like having a family!

249
00:17:58,300 --> 00:18:01,267
This is the only time
I've felt happiness!

250
00:18:02,533 --> 00:18:07,367
And I won't let you ruin
my life again!

251
00:18:07,500 --> 00:18:08,667
No!

252
00:18:08,800 --> 00:18:09,800
No!

253
00:18:10,900 --> 00:18:13,400
Emma couldn't do that,

254
00:18:14,900 --> 00:18:16,533
let alone you.

255
00:18:16,667 --> 00:18:22,267
Do you mean you took Emma away
from her family?

256
00:18:23,667 --> 00:18:25,367
You really are a monster.

257
00:18:25,500 --> 00:18:26,800
Monster!

258
00:18:26,933 --> 00:18:28,833
Monster!

259
00:18:28,967 --> 00:18:30,967
- Let go of me!
- I regret it!

260
00:18:31,100 --> 00:18:34,900
I regret I chose your side
and not Emma's!

261
00:18:35,033 --> 00:18:38,967
And I won't let you foo
my granddaughter, too!

262
00:18:39,100 --> 00:18:40,100
Auntie Jade?

263
00:18:40,233 --> 00:18:41,200
Grandmother?

264
00:18:43,800 --> 00:18:45,200
Auntie Jade?

265
00:18:47,700 --> 00:18:49,633
Let go.

266
00:18:49,767 --> 00:18:51,000
Ligaya!

267
00:18:51,133 --> 00:18:52,000
Mom?

268
00:18:54,367 --> 00:18:55,133
Emma?

269
00:18:56,667 --> 00:18:58,600
I dreamed of Mom.

270
00:18:58,733 --> 00:18:59,800
Ligaya, wait!

271
00:18:59,933 --> 00:19:01,967
Mookie!

272
00:19:11,000 --> 00:19:12,000
Grandmother!

273
00:19:13,133 --> 00:19:14,633
Are you there?

274
00:19:20,467 --> 00:19:21,933
Auntie Jade?

275
00:19:26,800 --> 00:19:28,200
Grandmother! Are you there?

276
00:19:28,367 --> 00:19:29,100
Mookie!

277
00:19:32,667 --> 00:19:35,133
Auntie Jade,
is Grandmother there?

278
00:19:35,267 --> 00:19:39,000
I think I heard her calling me.

279
00:19:39,133 --> 00:19:41,767
And I heard people yelling.

280
00:19:44,033 --> 00:19:47,600
I was talking to your
grandmother over the phone.

281
00:19:47,733 --> 00:19:50,833
We were on loudspeaker.
Maybe that's what you heard.

282
00:19:51,200 --> 00:19:56,900
I was asking her to come home.
But she didn't want to.

283
00:19:57,033 --> 00:19:59,867
What did she say? Where is she?

284
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:03,200
She went back to Cebu.

285
00:20:05,067 --> 00:20:09,800
She still can't accept
that Emma left us.

286
00:20:09,933 --> 00:20:14,467
And she still can't accept
your dad and me.

287
00:20:17,767 --> 00:20:23,433
She told me I ruined your
family.

288
00:20:25,233 --> 00:20:28,500
Auntie, forget it.

289
00:20:29,567 --> 00:20:31,433
You didn't do anything wrong.

290
00:20:45,667 --> 00:20:48,400
Come on, let's do something.

291
00:20:48,533 --> 00:20:49,833
Let's go out?

292
00:20:49,967 --> 00:20:51,367
Really?

293
00:20:51,500 --> 00:20:52,867
Go get changed.

294
00:20:53,000 --> 00:20:54,200
Okay.

295
00:21:18,867 --> 00:21:20,133
Are you okay now?

296
00:21:25,800 --> 00:21:29,767
Mom wasn't there when they
brought me to the center.

297
00:21:31,267 --> 00:21:33,200
I didn't see her again.

298
00:21:35,333 --> 00:21:37,667
Why did I dream of her?

299
00:21:38,900 --> 00:21:42,500
I don't understand,
but I feel nervous.

300
00:21:42,667 --> 00:21:44,933
Maybe your mom
is thinking of you.

301
00:21:46,000 --> 00:21:47,133
I hope so.

302
00:21:49,000 --> 00:21:50,700
I wonder how she's doing.

303
00:21:58,033 --> 00:21:59,100
Ligaya.

304
00:22:00,133 --> 00:22:00,967
You're awake now.

305
00:22:02,200 --> 00:22:03,367
Don't worry.

306
00:22:04,700 --> 00:22:07,167
I won't let you starve.

307
00:22:07,300 --> 00:22:11,467
But you can't go out
of the room.

308
00:22:13,900 --> 00:22:16,967
It's your fault, Ligaya.

309
00:22:17,133 --> 00:22:23,933
This wouldn't have happened to
you if you accepted me as Olive

310
00:22:24,067 --> 00:22:26,933
and chose to make it up
to me and cooperate.

311
00:22:29,033 --> 00:22:32,000
I'm really sorry, Ligaya.

312
00:22:32,133 --> 00:22:35,367
You won't be basking in
the sun for a while.

313
00:22:35,500 --> 00:22:37,133
But don't worry.

314
00:22:37,267 --> 00:22:41,367
I'll get you vitamin D
supplements from the pharmacy.

315
00:22:41,500 --> 00:22:44,167
You're evil! Evil!

316
00:22:44,300 --> 00:22:47,167
Remember, be a good girl.

317
00:22:50,167 --> 00:22:51,933
Bye, for now, Ligaya.

318
00:22:52,067 --> 00:22:54,033
Don't leave me here!

319
00:22:54,167 --> 00:22:55,000
Hey!

320
00:23:00,867 --> 00:23:03,933
Don't forget, be a good girl...

321
00:23:04,067 --> 00:23:05,633
and be quiet.

322
00:23:15,100 --> 00:23:19,867
Guys, if you want to order
anything, it's on me.

323
00:23:21,767 --> 00:23:23,633
Because...

324
00:23:23,767 --> 00:23:27,367
thank you, Auntie Jade!

325
00:23:28,467 --> 00:23:30,133
Why do you still have a picture
of Emma on your phone?

326
00:23:30,700 --> 00:23:32,733
Didn't I tell you to delete
everything?

327
00:23:32,867 --> 00:23:34,733
Darn you, Emma.

328
00:23:34,867 --> 00:23:36,900
I hope you never come back.

329
00:23:37,033 --> 00:23:38,833
I hope you're already dead.

330
00:23:39,900 --> 00:23:44,433
Ladies and gentlemen, the new
manager of Bites and Bottles,

331
00:23:44,567 --> 00:23:46,033
Emma Joseco.

332
00:23:47,867 --> 00:23:49,767
Mookie, what's going on
with you?

333
00:23:49,900 --> 00:23:52,267
You're no longer the Mookie
I know.

334
00:23:52,400 --> 00:23:53,800
You've changed a lot, Mooks.

335
00:23:53,933 --> 00:23:54,867
And so?

336
00:23:55,000 --> 00:23:56,833
Don't you want to be
your friend anymore?

337
00:23:57,000 --> 00:23:58,100
Is that it?

338
00:23:58,233 --> 00:23:59,967
DJ!

339
00:24:00,100 --> 00:24:01,700
One more, please!

340
00:24:03,333 --> 00:24:05,367
Let's dance, girls!
